{"DUG":[{"def":"A teat, pap, or nipple; -- formerly that of a human mother, now that of a cow or other beast.","pos":""}],"DUGONG":[{"def":"An aquatic herbivorous mammal (Halicore dugong), of the order Sirenia, allied to the manatee, but with a bilobed tail.","pos":""}],"DUGOUT":[{"def":"A canoe or boat dug out from a large log.","pos":""},{"def":"A place dug out.","pos":""}],"DUGWAY":[{"def":"A way or road dug through a hill, or sunk below the surface of the land.","pos":""}]}